column3:
This bugfix can not be tested, because none of our RPCs accept nested dictionaries. However, the following diff might help:

```diff
diff --git a/src/wallet/rpcdump.cpp b/src/wallet/rpcdump.cpp
index 9c5dae3623..81d282ceca 100644
--- a/src/wallet/rpcdump.cpp
+++ b/src/wallet/rpcdump.cpp
@@ -1377,7 +1377,7 @@ UniValue importmulti(const JSONRPCRequest& mainRequest)

Aha, thanks -- this looks exactly like the problem I was seeing with "range", which _was_ a nested dictionary at the time of my last rebase, even though it didn't exist in 0.17, and is a nested array on master.\n\nKudos for finding the problem despite the repro being missing. :-)
